snippet.textDisplay: Do the water birth!!! It's ALL about the breathing. During your Braxton hicks contractions practice your breathing. Alot of women tend to clench and stop breathing through any kind of contractions that they experience during pregnancy, before & during delivery. I had my first and only child at my home with 2 midwives & my man. I Didn't do any classes, all I did was practice my breathing. Everytime I felt a pre-contraction, I took DEEP breaths to stretch out the cramp. Learn to concentrate on your breathing, maybe start practicing more meditation if you haven't already. DON'T give birth on your back, that's the MOST painful way to give birth, which is so convenient as to why doctors make you lay in bed while coping with contractions, which in result will influence the desire for a epidural. I gave birth in doggie style position & all it took was 3 pushes & my man was there to catch the baby from behind lol. Squatting, laying on your side or in doggie position is the best way to push. Most importantly, listen to your body, the only reason why I gave birth in doggie position was because any other way hurt me too much. If you manage to give birth in the water awesome, but personally, I would only use it to take a break from back to back contractions, as sitting in warm water slows contractions down. I was in labor for 2 & half days due to my daughter plugging the hole, with her head, that tore when my water broke. I would recommend a nice warm bathtub or pool & then another area that is comfortable to breathe through your contractions get on your knees & rock back in forth & even give birth if you feel that it is most comfortable FOR YOU. Obviously it will have to be an area where you wouldn't care if blood and bodily fluids get all over. I gave birth on my bed but I had a mattress protector to protect my mattress as well as towels & those doggie pad things. Good luck!!! Home births truly are a beautiful thing & doing that in your new home will add that much more sentimental value to your home!!!
